.TH "d_namespace_path" 9 "d_namespace_path" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
d_namespace_path \- lookup a name associated with a given path
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" d_namespace_path
.BI "(const struct path *path "  ","
.BI "char *buf "  ","
.BI "char **name "  ","
.BI "int flags "  ","
.BI "const char *disconnected "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "path" 12
path to lookup  (NOT NULL)
.IP "buf" 12
buffer to store path to  (NOT NULL)
.IP "name" 12
Returns - pointer for start of path name with in \fIbuf\fP (NOT NULL)
.IP "flags" 12
flags controlling path lookup
.IP "disconnected" 12
string to prefix to disconnected paths
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Handle path name lookup.
.SH "RETURN"
0 else error code if path lookup fails
When no error the path name is returned in \fIname\fP which points to
to a position in \fIbuf\fP
